subject: World Cup (Skiing)
lead_paragraph: Jean-Baptiste Grange of France won a World Cup slalom Saturday in Wengen, Switzerland, capturing his second victory in two days. He easily held off Jens Byggmark of Sweden, finishing with a combined time of 1 minute 34.81 seconds. Grange won Friday’s super-combi for the second World Cup victory of his career.
